the villain in this story.

00:36:10.126 --> 00:36:13.171
I think I wanted us to work out
because I was holding onto the past.

00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:15.715
But I have a new path now.

00:36:17.300 --> 00:36:19.176
- One I have to face alone.
- Enid, I...

00:36:19.177 --> 00:36:20.553
[sighs sadly]

00:36:21.137 --> 00:36:22.680
Killer dress, by the way.

00:36:26.309 --> 00:36:28.519
[elegant classical music
playing in distance]

00:36:29.145 --> 00:36:30.730
[disembodied sobbing]

00:36:34.525 --> 00:36:35.526
Agnes?

00:36:36.485 --> 00:36:39.238
I can't even get peace
and solitude in a crime scene.

00:36:40.489 --> 00:36:41.489
What happened to you?

00:36:41.490 --> 00:36:43.993
Wednesday dropped an Addams bomb on me.

00:36:44.660 --> 00:36:46.913
Congrats. You win.

00:36:47.538 --> 00:36:50.582
I thought I was everything she wanted
in a best friend.

00:36:50.583 --> 00:36:53.251
Sarcastic, sardonic,

00:36:53.252 --> 00:36:55.755
with the same dark neogoth aesthetic.

00:36:56.339 --> 00:36:57.881
A task-oriented clue hound,

00:36:57.882 --> 00:36:59.883
willing to risk life and limb

00:36:59.884 --> 00:37:02.637
in a relentless pursuit
of solving the case.

00:37:03.679 --> 00:37:07.725
[sobs softly] But it turns out...
I was dead wrong.

00:37:10.102 --> 00:37:13.063
One Wednesday Addams
is more than enough for this world.

00:37:13.064 --> 00:37:15.232
If you're tired of being invisible,

00:37:15.233 --> 00:37:17.984
